latestIgtvVideos.title: Let’s #StopTheBeautyTest
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Please take a couple of minutes and watch this powerful film with undivided attention. We all need to 🙌

Ever since we’re born, women in India are put under the beauty scanner. I’ve been there. The conditioning is so immense and the stereotypes are so internalized, that as a girl grows up, she’s often called out for aspects of her external self, that don’t quite align with what society deems fit.
And so, these ideals of beauty govern our lives and teach us the harshest of lessons in rejection and insufficiency.

This is especially highlighted in the arranged marriage process where women are rejected based on their physical qualities.
It’s a brutal test that dismisses women at face value, often in ways that can leave the woman feeling inadequate even though she may be comfortable in her own skin.

It’s time we rewrite these ideals and #StopTheBeautyTest.

Join #DoveIndia ‘s latest movement and amplify the message that there cannot be one definition of beauty. How can there be, when we’re all so beautiful in our differences, sizes, shapes and body types?

#AD #GraziaXDove #feminaxdove

latestIgtvVideos.title: Keep Exploring ft. My Bombay 🤗
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Put together this little film a couple months ago when I was asked to explain what #KeepExploring means to me.
I looked at the words and couldn't help but see them in the context of last year, the pandemic, and how they've both forced the explorer in me to be more fluid, present and accepting of what's around me, rather than what's miles away.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Here's to the World Outside 🌻
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
August was quite the downer. I allowed myself to be sucked into the negatives, until I woke up one day last week and consciously sought out all the blessings life has given me. All the lessons Travel has taught me. And all the gifts the World has given me. Teacher’s Day or not, I guess this video is from a student of the global classroom, thanking the many teachers she has learnt from on the road.

I opened my Hard Disk and began watching my old travel footage. Ladakh, Kyrgyzstan, Indonesia, Kerala, Sikkim, Uzbekistan, Oman, Australia…these weren’t just places. They were feelings, memories, documents of survival and triumph, defeat and resurrection, flying, soaring, living, loving. 

My soul saw that it had been fed well, my heart knew that I was bigger than the negatives, and my mind knew that I had chosen to sink, just as I could choose to float and fly again.

And then I chanced upon this beautiful song by @tomrosenthal1
It resonated so hard with me. We do forget the little things in life, the little everyday loves that spark joys and add up to big moments. That feeling when your adrenaline rushes through your body like a jolt of lightening. The way your mom’s rasam tastes after a month of nasi goreng. The way a stranger hugs you and guides you back to health with a sternness usually reserved for mothers and nurses. The way a double humped Bactrian camel gives you wet, sloppy kisses. The way the clouds make shapes as you lie down on fresh grass. The stare-off with a shark in the depths of the ocean, no life jacket, only love and faith. The way that maggi hits on a cold, snowy morning in the mountains. The strange satisfaction of watching a leech feed itself on your foot, leaving a trail of red. Scents that tickle your nose as you zipline past crop fields in Punjab.

Memories are potent, hold on to them.
The past is here to tide us through the present, and I hope we consciously look outside windows and seek magic in the world outside of our pockets.

I hope this video lifts you up, the process of making it sure healed me.

Share this with anyone who might need a warm hug of words and far-flung places :)

latestIgtvVideos.title: #WithdrawEIA2020 A simplified understanding of EIA2020
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Hi India, we have exactly 8 more days to send in our objections and call for the Withdrawal of EIA 2020.

Unless you've been living under a rock,  you've probably seen countless posts and videos of dissent, because as citizens of this democracy, we have a constitutional right to comment on the problematic new Draft of the Environment Impact Assessment norms.

I made this video to help amplify, and give you a simplified understanding of the 83 page Draft, so you can get a quick look at why environmentalists and experts are so deeply concerned by it. I've tried to keep away from the jargon, and give you a short, crisp and easy synopsis of some of the key points of contention, and why WE, (internet-using, English and Hindi speaking folks) need to send out that objection email ASAP.
Also please do Share this video and other pieces of communication on #WithdrawEIA2020 , so we can get more people to send in that email!

I hope this helps you understand it and gets you curious to read up more and take action.
The Draft is up on the internet, and multiple posters, podcasts, videos and lives have summarised the key problem points, because this is the final mile and we Must amplify and get more people to send that email!

LINK IN BIO for the ready-made email draft. (Change a few words in the subject and body to avoid spam bounce-backs)
Email to eia2020-moefcc@gov.in

Huge shoutout to @letindiabreathe.in and @fridaysforfuture.india for not only relentlessly fighting the good fight, but also for supporting me through the making of this video, verifying my research and running it past lawyers as well.

More shoutouts to @mirchi_suchi @sonali.jain @radxbone @dollysingh @shivya @abhiandniyu for fighting the good fight and encouraging more people to raise their voices against EIA2020.

8 days to go. Let's do this!
#WithdrawEIA2020 #ScrapEIA2020

latestPosts.caption:
Freediving with WHALE SHARKS in Maldives! 💙

Always such a dream to be able to spot them in the wild and get uninterrupted minutes watching them swim in shallow depths as they come looking for warm water.

This time, I went out on 3 back to back days in South Ari Atoll to try and spot them, and we saw them EVERYDAY 😭 This is the atoll you want to be in to up your chances to spot them throughout the year. Dhigurah is a gorgeous local island with the longest beach you’ll see, base yourself there.

The first clip is with a whale shark I was able to ID with the help of @maldiveswhalesharkresearch , as Fenuparee :)
We swam with him for 25-30 full minutes. He just kept going and so did we, and a moment aligned where I got that first video. It’s like spotting a chunk of the midnight starry sky, suspended underwater 🥹 Absolute magic.

They’re the BIGGEST fish and shark in the ocean, but the gentlest giants you’ll ever see.
Add this to your bucketlist!

Trip with the awesome @oceanholic_divers @white_sand_dhigurah 

Videos on @gopro @goproindia Hero11 and Hero10 Black, by @katerina_top @allforblueorg and me :)

This country kept blowing my mind 🤯

The more I travel, the more I’m convinced how little we know of places, and how one dimensional our perceptions can be.

In a small, obscure town 90 minutes out of Chengdu, is this stunningly designed book store (inside a random mall?!!)

China, you’re so much more than your Govt.
Your people are talented, and I got a taste of it in every possible way, including design 💯

Reality >>>>> Videos 🤯

This is Heaven’s Gate at the Tianmen mountains in China’s Hunan Province. And the light show right after sunset is a Magical MARVEL that videos do zero justice to!

Gosh, we just stood there for 30 minutes as it got progressively colder, wondering if part of our shivering was just because of the spectacular light show in front of us.

It’s larger than life, and there weren’t all that many people either. Just bonkers!

We walked down 999 steps from the top to make it down in time for the first lights. Surreal!

Trippiest new experience for you, your kids or just even as a solo outing in Bangkok ♥️

Absolutely loved this immersive, interactive 3D experience at the Space and Time Cube+
Tickets cost around 599 Baht for an adult, and you get over an hour inside the many rooms!

Save and go!

The one where I did Coachella with @googlepixel 🥹
This weekend last year, so much nostalgia 🫶

Throwback to one of those chapters in life I’ll Always be grateful for! During possibly the toughest time in my life, I got this small window of opportunity to embrace pure love, music, joy and good vibes! And boy did I jump on it!
Flew all the way across the world for a 6 day trip to paradise 🎡

Here’s a dump cos I’m missing it all SO much!

PS: I didn’t know who Sabrina Carpenter was until I watched her kill it on stage and literally launch Espresso- the song of the year 😁

latestPosts.caption:
Would this work in India?
Is THIS how I’ll find a husband? 🌝

Honestly, I found this a bit odd. Guess it kinda works in China because apparently there are a few of these around the country.
Arranged marriages are a thing in their society too, but to have all details out like this in public? Imagine the privacy compromise and stalking-possibilities 🤯

Thanks but no thanks!

For a second though, imagine this with me. A society and people who aren’t creeps. They respect privacy and are decent human beings. No misuse of data.

THEN imagine this even to date and find like-minded partners to hang out with. Wake up and head to the park- do your walk/workout- walk your dog- and BAM! Scan through profiles IRL, call one you like, live happily ever after 😛

No? Okay sorry it’s Sunday and I’m just dreaming kbyeeee!

#China #MarriageMarket #Dating

Swachh Bharat kab? 🥲

We keep saying the sheer size of our population is the problem, na?
I couldn’t help but observe how CLEAN China is.
Even the smaller cities and towns. The national parks. The random back alleys.

Z E R O  T R A S H.

Yes, they’re heavily controlled and regulations and rules are super strict. I get that. But some enforced laws do help, and I wonder if we could really instil this behavioural change at a ground level? Someday? When? 💔

Sorry Amma 😂🙈

Two hundred sixty metres.
99% of the internet will show you Macau Tower as the highest bungy in the world. 233 metres.

No, sir. 260 metres. China. THIS is the highest bungy in the world. Even the rope is longer and more loose, making the fall and drop even longer and deeper.

Apparently there’s ANOTHER newer one somewhere in China that’s 360 metres but the rope is tighter, making this one technically the highest in the world (couldn’t find this on the internet at all though :/)

The rope here wasn’t even tethered to my foot as it usually is. It was SUCH an easy, light fall with no yanks anywhere on my person. I didn’t feel a thing. The huggy bag was a bonus at the end 😂

I was terrified of doing this. Having bungy-ed twice before, last one in Australia in 2019, somewhere my fear grew. Because I had read some horror stories of lower back issues and what not.

But we saw this and I decided I needed to fight this fear before it festered more. SO glad I did!!!

PS: This was the ONLY tourist attraction where there was one staff member (a Nepalese guy) who spoke English. Made my anxiety a lot better to be able to talk to him before the plunge. Phew!

PPS: this cost 2000 yuan, aka around 24,000 INR. Worth every penny.

📍Zhangjiajie
